## Behavioral contract

Add the universal content-page route handler. One file, serves every URL not claimed by a more-specific route.

### Route location

`app/(site)/[...slug]/page.tsx`

Next.js resolves specific routes before dynamic ones, so static routes (`/`, `/gatherer`, `/search`, `/critiques`, `/vocab`, `/xenotext`, etc.) continue to win. This catch-all serves anything else, including multi-segment URLs.

### Behavior

```tsx
import type { Metadata } from 'next';
import { notFound } from 'next/navigation';
import { CalendarDays, Clock, ShieldCheck, BookOpen } from 'lucide-react';
import { MarkdownRenderer } from '@/components/mdx/markdown-renderer';
import { HeroMeta } from '@/components/site/hero-meta';
import { PageToc } from '@/components/site/page-toc';
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { getContentPageBySlug, allContentPagesSorted } from '@/lib/content';

interface PageProps {
  params: { slug: string[] };
}

export function generateStaticParams() {
  return allContentPagesSorted().map((doc) => ({
    slug: doc.slug.split('/'),
  }));
}

export function generateMetadata({ params }: PageProps): Metadata {
  const doc = getContentPageBySlug(params.slug.join('/'));
  if (!doc) return {};
  return {
    title: `${doc.title} - Elden Ring Is The Large Glass`,
    description: doc.summary,
  };
}

export default function ContentPage({ params }: PageProps) {
  const doc = getContentPageBySlug(params.slug.join('/'));
  if (!doc) notFound();

  const sealStatus =
    doc.ethereumAttestation && doc.bitcoinOts
      ? 'Sealed on Bitcoin and Ethereum'
      : doc.ethereumAttestation
      ? 'Attested on Ethereum'
      : doc.bitcoinOts
      ? 'Timestamped on Bitcoin'
      : null;

  return (
    <div className="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_220px] lg:gap-8">
      <div className="space-y-10">
        <section className="glass-card border border-[var(--border-emphasis)] bg-gradient-to-b from-[rgb(var(--bg-secondary-rgb)/0.9)] to-[rgb(var(--bg-secondary-rgb)/0.6)] p-8 lg:p-12">
          <div className="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
            <div className="max-w-3xl flex-1">
              {doc.eyebrow && (
                <div className="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                  <BookOpen className="h-5 w-5 text-[var(--accent-gold)]" />
                  <p className="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-[var(--text-tertiary)]">
                    {doc.eyebrow}
                  </p>
                </div>
              )}
              <h1 className="page-hero-title">{doc.title}</h1>
              {doc.subtitle && <p className="mt-4 page-hero-description">{doc.subtitle}</p>}
            </div>
            {doc.hashableFile && (
              <Button asChild variant="outline" size="sm">
                <a href={`/proofs/${doc.hashableFile}`} download>Download source</a>
              </Button>
            )}
          </div>
          <HeroMeta
            items={[
              { label: 'Updated', value: new Date(doc.updated).toLocaleDateString(), icon: CalendarDays },
              ...(doc.readingMinutes ? [{ label: 'Reading Time', value: `${doc.readingMinutes} min`, icon: Clock }] : []),
              ...(sealStatus ? [{ label: 'Status', value: sealStatus, icon: ShieldCheck }] : []),
            ]}
          />
        </section>

        <MarkdownRenderer code={doc.body.code} />
      </div>

      <aside className="hidden lg:block">
        <PageToc headings={doc.headings} />
      </aside>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Notes

- For **mobile**, render the TOC above the hero in a `<details>` — add that as a separate element conditionally visible below `lg`. The PageToc component from Pebble 0.3 handles both shapes internally; call it once and let its internal responsive CSS do the switching. (Pebble 0.3 delivered a component that handles both; integrate accordingly.)
- Sealed-doc hero adds "Download source" button and "Status" HeroMeta item driven purely by frontmatter presence. No manual per-page chrome.
- `ManuscriptDisplay` is NOT injected by this route. It is a registered MDX component (Pebble 0.2); pages that want it invoke it inline in the MDX body.
- `HashVerification` is also NOT injected by this route. Same story — MDX body invokes it with explicit props.

## Preconditions

- Pebble 0.1 (ContentPage + getters)
- Pebble 0.2 (MarkdownRenderer upgrades, so double-wrapping doesn't happen)
- Pebble 0.3 (PageToc + headings computed field)

## Scope / non-goals

- Do NOT migrate any MDX content in this pebble. The route renders correctly against an empty `content/pages/` dir; Phase 1 and 2 populate it.
- Do NOT delete any legacy page.tsx files yet. Static routes still win; catch-all only serves paths not claimed by them.
- Do NOT add the staging `/preview/...` route here (Pebble 0.5).

## Acceptance criteria

1. `app/(site)/[...slug]/page.tsx` exists and exports default + generateMetadata + generateStaticParams.
2. `content/pages/_test.mdx` with frontmatter `{ title: 'Test', summary: 'Test.', updated: 2026-04-14 }` and body `## A heading\n\nSome text.` produces a working `/\_test` URL:
   - renders hero with title + Updated meta item
   - renders body prose
   - renders TOC (right-rail on desktop) listing "A heading"
3. `npm run build` passes.
4. `npm run typecheck` passes.
5. Static routes still serve their original pages (verify `/gatherer`, `/search`, `/critiques`, `/`, `/about`).
6. A URL with no matching MDX (e.g. `/does-not-exist`) returns 404 via `notFound()`.

Remove the `_test.mdx` before the commit.
